{"title": "Einstein and the Universe", "description": "\"M. Nordmann has presented Einstein\u2019s principle in words which lift the average reader over many of the difficulties he must encounter in trying to take it in. Remembering Goethe\u2019s maxim that he who would accomplish anything must limit himself, he has not aimed at covering the full field to which Einstein\u2019s teaching is directed. But he succeeds in making many abstruse things intelligible to the layman.\"   - Summary by from the Preface by Viscount Haldane\r\n<br><br>\r\nGiving significant credit to Henri Poincar\u00e9 and others whose work provided some of the basis from which Einstein developed his Special and General Theories of Relativity, Nordmann provides easily grasped examples to explain complex phenomena outside the grasp of the non-physicist.  Finally, he compares and contrasts the Relativist vs. Newtonian interpretation of the world.  (Summary by J. M. Smallheer)", "duration": 18719, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17001", "name": "Charles Nordmann"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/einsteinandtheuniverse_2209_librivox/einsteinuniverse_2209.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Astronomy", "Physics & Mechanics"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Krista Zaleski"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Preface by Viscount Richard Burton Haldane", "readers": [688], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/einsteinandtheuniverse_2209_librivox/einsteinandtheuniverse_01_nordmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 368}, {"section": 2, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [688], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/einsteinandtheuniverse_2209_librivox/einsteinandtheuniverse_02_nordmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 315}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Metmorphoses of Space and Time", "readers": [688], "pa